1
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:04,959
He swore to me and my mother

2
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,480
that the surgery was a success.

3
00:01:08,879 --> 00:01:10,799
But after my mother got off the operating table,

4
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
not long after, she hemorrhaged and couldn't be saved.

5
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:22,280
I'll never forget the agonizing look

6
00:01:22,359 --> 00:01:23,719
on my mother's face in that hospital bed.

7
00:01:24,719 --> 00:01:26,959
And it's all thanks to your father.

8
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:31,680
Mitral valve:

9
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:33,079
severe stenosis.

10
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:35,319
Aortic valve:

11
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,079
moderate stenosis,

12
00:01:37,439 --> 00:01:38,480
with moderate regurgitation.

13
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:40,000
Complicated by atrial fibrillation.

14
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,480
Her mother was only 47 at the time.

15
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:46,640
She simply couldn't undergo lifelong anticoagulation.

16
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,359
Complex aortic root reconstruction surgery

17
00:01:49,439 --> 00:01:50,840
was the only option that could maximize

18
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:53,159
the patient's quality of life.

19
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:55,200
I once thought something went wrong

20
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,480
during the surgery itself.

21
00:01:56,799 --> 00:01:57,959
But as the attending physician,

22
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:58,920
from start to finish,

23
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,640
did he ever speak up? No, he didn't.

24
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:06,159
That surgery took me a full five hours.

25
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,840
I remember every single detail clearly.

26
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,840
Every metric, intraoperative and postoperative,

27
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,759
was within controllable limits.

28
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:15,560
Even if her mother

29
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:17,319
were here today questioning me in person,

30
00:02:17,479 --> 00:02:18,680
my answer would be the same.

31
00:02:18,919 --> 00:02:19,680
I made no mistakes.

32
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,960
I didn't make a single mistake.

33
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,120
She had severe oral issues before the surgery.

34
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:26,520
At every consultation,

35
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,960
I reminded you over and over again.

36
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:29,960
Her condition

37
00:02:30,039 --> 00:02:31,840
could very likely lead to postoperative infection.

38
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:32,919
And what about you?

39
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:33,240
What did you do?

40
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,400
Just so this case

41
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:37,000
could make it in time for your Specialist certification,

42
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,360
you chose to turn a blind eye.

43
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:42,240
You think this is the outcome I wanted?

44
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,560
This isn't what I wanted either.

45
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,560
Unexpected outcomes can happen to anyone.

46
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:56,960
You've spent your whole life chasing

47
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,400
a perfect surgical success rate.

48
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,719
Do you know why I left Pingjin back then?

49
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,400
Because after that surgery,

50
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,400
I finally saw you for who you really are.

51
00:03:08,719 --> 00:03:10,000
You're too obsessive.

52
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,240
If she'd just waited a few more months,

53
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,159
if she'd waited until her periodontitis

54
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,960
had completely healed,

55
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,960
she could've had the surgery.

56
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,719
But your father,

57
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:27,199
it was your father who told my mother

58
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,719
the chance of postoperative infection was negligible.

59
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,719
But it was that exact negligible chance

60
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:37,400
that took my mother's life.

61
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,400
I hate your father to the core.

62
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:43,919
I've hated him for ten years.

63
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:46,400
But I hate myself even more.

64
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,039
Why didn't I convince my mother

65
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:51,280
to just wait a little longer?

66
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:52,840
Wait?

67
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,080
Could her condition afford to wait?

68
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:57,280
You knew her condition back then!

69
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,879
Every day of delay added more risk!

70
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,199
You don't need to explain anymore.

71
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:16,680
You can call me selfish and obsessive,

72
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,879
or say my skills are inadequate,

73
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:21,399
but I will never allow anyone

74
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:23,360
to question my professional integrity.

75
00:04:24,199 --> 00:04:25,120
I, Jiang Zhaohe,

76
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,160
have always been open and aboveboard.

77
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,000
Unlike you,

78
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,959
deliberately placing that girl

79
00:04:31,079 --> 00:04:32,480
right next to my son.

80
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,199
What exactly are your intentions?

81
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,079
This is just fate.

82
00:04:36,639 --> 00:04:37,319
Fate?

83
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,079
Let me tell you,

84
00:04:40,759 --> 00:04:42,079
don't you even think about letting my son

85
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:43,959
stay here with you,

86
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,279
to become a

87
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,279
freak like you!

88
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,279
Feier

89
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,439
Uncle Jiang

90
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,720
What are you doing here?

91
00:05:15,279 --> 00:05:17,519
Why? Now, whenever I...

92
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:19,639
Whenever I close my eyes,

93
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:20,959
I...

94
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:24,199
I think of my mother.

95
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,639
I think of her crying out for help.

96
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,079
That kind of despair...

97
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:30,920
You could never understand.

98
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:31,879
Tang Yi.

99
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:36,920
Deep breath.

100
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,240
Deep breath.

101
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:40,439
Deep breaths. Deep breaths.

102
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,680
Deep breath.

103
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,560
If

104
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,480
I hadn't met Director Zeng,

105
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,759
I might

106
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,759
have spent my whole life

107
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,240
unable to move past

108
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:19,240
my mother's passing.

109
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,439
He told me

110
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,000
that hatred

111
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:29,680
and regret shouldn't consume my entire life.

112
00:06:36,839 --> 00:06:38,399
Although nothing can be changed,

113
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,519
but

114
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:47,040
when my mother and I

115
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:49,160
had nowhere to turn for help,

116
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:52,160
the only one who gave us hope

117
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,040
was also your father.

118
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,240
We've

119
00:07:05,079 --> 00:07:05,879
met before, haven't we?

120
00:07:24,639 --> 00:07:25,399
Mom

121
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,120
Mom

122
00:07:28,959 --> 00:07:30,079
Mom

123
00:07:33,639 --> 00:07:34,800
Mom

124
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:39,679
Tang Yi

125
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:56,360
Don't touch me!

